  "body": "This is a feature request:\r\n\r\nSometimes, it's necessary set a DOM property rather than an attribute. I have come across this more and more in the upcoming trend of Web Components / Custom Elements.\r\nRight now, this can only be done using a ref (e.g. `myRef.current.myProperty = \"foo\"`).\r\n\r\nIn Vue, this can be done using the [.prop modifier](https://vuejs.org/v2/api/#v-bind):\r\n\r\n    <my-custom-element :foo.prop=\"bar\" />",
